# How to use hex to type bits more quickly
Maddie demonstrates how to use the hexadecimal number system to encode colors.  Reminder: hex is not a compression scheme - it doesn't not change the underlying binary code.  Hex is a useful way to view bits because we can represent a 4-bit chunk with a single character.

